<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by Siraj Ahmed Shaik (WSC005)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 30pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Siraj</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Ahmed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Shaik</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (WSC005)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This evidence has a primary focus on computer science, which is an important STEM subject and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">underpins a large majority of professional roles in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Information Technology (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">IT</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">industry both in private and public sectors. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Some of the key messages included in this evidence are summarised as follows</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#a6a6a6; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.28pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Computer Science suffers from a ‘masculine’ image that serves to convey an area of work and study that is not very inclusive of women</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="color:#a6a6a6; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.28pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Computer Science education, both at school and university, is also a critical factor to discourage women from entering IT careers, undermining confidence and self-esteem</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">; </span></li><li style="color:#a6a6a6; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.28pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There is a serious lack of female role models in the IT industry, which in turn re</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">duces suitable mentoring opportunities;</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and</span></li><li style="color:#a6a6a6; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 30.28pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The competitive nature of the IT industry, as with other technology and professionally competitive sectors, offers fewer opportunities for a work-family life balance, which serves to put off many female professio</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nals</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">All of the above issues are systematically addressed in dedicated sections </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">below. This is followed by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a set of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">brief </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recommendations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 24pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The final item in this document is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a list o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">f references</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that have been </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">consulted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for compiling this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">document. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is important as it serves as a set of surveys, scientific observations an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d studies, and research contributions, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that form the basis of a set of coherent views presented in this document. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Author</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (and Declaration of Interest)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This evidence is submitted in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">personal capacity by Dr. Siraj Ahmed Shaikh, who is a Reader in the Department of Computing at the Faculty of Engineering and Computing, Coventry University, Coventry, UK. He has been actively involved in teaching and research of computer science for over </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">12 years. He holds a PhD in Computer Science and a MA in Higher and Professional Education. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">He is a Chartered Scientist (Member of the Science Council) and a Chartered Fellow of the BCS-The Chartered Institute of IT. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As part of his day-to-day professional</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> activities, he works with female colleagues (both senior and junior in rank), and female students (in class room and one-to-one supervisory capacity).</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The set of views and opinions presented in this document </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">belong solely to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">author and do not represen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the views of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Coventry University.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Image P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">roblem</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">From a philosophical perspective, computer science has been criticised from a feminist perspective and called ‘another masculine science’. The underlying epistemology – the nature of knowledge – for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the subject has been shown to be ‘masculinist’ and ‘decontextualised from its objects of study’, attributed with abstraction, reductionism, sacredness and value-freeness. Such </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">characterisations reinforce traditional </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">stereotype of science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as an exclusive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">do</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">main of male scientists.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">education process does not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">help the image problem either. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The subject is typically aligned with mathematics and e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ngineering, carrying forward a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ‘pure’ and ‘masculine’ image as students progress through school and university education. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">At school, there is some evidence to suggest that there is a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">general lack of enjoyment of computer use by girls, not helped by a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lack of well-trained I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">T teachers an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d staff. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 24pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A contributing factor is also to do with the associated professional culture</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, which in the case of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">computer science </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is seen as highly demanding, male dominated, individually isolating, ‘nerdy’ and ‘boring’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">do</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">es</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> not help school girls’ percep</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tion of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">IT</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">profession </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">who are encouraged to make early career choices in an increasingly competitive world. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Confid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ence and S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">elf-E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">steem</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">evidence of lack of self-belief and confidence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> female students in their ability to perform </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and progress </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in computer science as a subject. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Surveys show</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> this gap between perceived and actual ability </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of female students despite being successful in the discipline. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The findings include</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female students are less likely to correct a professor in cla</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ss than their</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> male counterparts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lack of self-confidence in software programming abilities in female students</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, which lies at the heart of many high-paid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> IT jobs.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 24pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A lack of an adequate number of women is in itself an excluding factor for women from a subject. A critical mass is necessary for a particular subgroup to influence the group it belongs to in any way. In order for women to constructively participate in the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> discourse and reshape gender relations in classrooms, a critical mass of women is necessary among men. Studies have shown, while examining various </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">university </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">departmental characteristics that affect retention of female students, computer science departmen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ts with a higher number of female students are more likely to retain them</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as gender-related perceptions and tensions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are less likely to be prevalent. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of Role Models</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">An aspect of the critical mass factor, which serves as both a cause and a consequen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ce of it, is the lack of mentoring and female role models in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">computer science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. The media coverage of the IT industry moguls, like Bill Gates and Steve Jobs (along with so many others – mostly men), projects an image of a male-dominated profession where wom</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">en are either not present at all or their achievements have not been significant. A lack of female role models propagates the masculine image further, one where only geeky, workaholic men, with no family or social responsibilities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> with an unethical ‘h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ackers’ mentality can survive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he role model process ought to start early for girls, with teachers at schools to act as examples of women working with computers. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Surveys on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gender and computer use in schools</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">find a correlation between the number of women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> teachers at school and the gender equality in terms of computer use. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">13</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The presence of female </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">academic staff </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in universities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is one important source of mentoring. Fresh new students look up to their lecturers and professors for inspiration and future guida</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nce. What better example of successful women in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">computer science </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">can be served t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o female students than their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tutors? </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Evidence suggests that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">this is particularly important as a positive higher education environment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">serves to inspire </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">positive fee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">dback is more important to them</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> than their male counterparts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 24pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ome other evidence suggests</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that university </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">departments with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">less </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">academics </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lost female student</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s at high rates relative to men</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Recent figures show that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in the UK </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">only one in 20 computin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g professors, one in eight computing researchers and one in four PhD students are female</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Reversing Trends</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">15</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">omputer science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as a discipline is unique, both in its history, as young but fast developing and, in its nature as problem-solving, algorithmic and technology-oriented. In recent years, its boundaries have expanded to overlap and adjoin a number of other disciplines, inc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">luding business and management (information systems), philosophy and psychology (human computer interaction and artificial intelligence), physiology (genetic algorithms and neural networks), digital art and graphics (multimedia and entertainment) and lingu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">istics, which have been traditionally outside the realm of science. It is important to observe this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">so that it offers a unique proposition for sustaining and welcoming many more women in IT-related careers, as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">opposed to traditional sciences and many other</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> STEM subjects</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 24pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">16</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The IT </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">industry more re</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cently has launched some encouraging initiatives </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which offer hope and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a bright future for a lot of women entering IT-related careers. The notable of these initiatives include The Google Anita Borg Memorial Scholarship</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, Grace Hopper Celebration of Women in Computing, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Athena SWAN (an initiative of the Equality Change Unit (ECU) and UK Research Councils (UKRC)) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and BCSWomen (a specialist group of the British Computer Society dedicated to women members). </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">17</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Computer Science, along with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">wider </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">range of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM subjects,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">need</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> an image makeover. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">coordinated </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">national effort is needed to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">address </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">this and raise the profile of STEM as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">progressive and welcoming careers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for women.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This has to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">realised thro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ugh a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> mix of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">top-down </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and bottom-up policy </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">initiatives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and should be a medium- to long-term goal. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">No quick fixes would serve to be effective. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">18</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The early years, through school and university education, are critical </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">if we</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are to allow women to raise confidenc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e and self-esteem.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A variety of areas need particular attention including </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">appropriate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">training</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of school staff in STEM subjects, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> mentoring</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">after-school </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">resources</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to overcome cultural and confidence issues for female students. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 24pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-22.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">19</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Large industry players, such as Google, IBM, Intel and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Microsoft</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are beginning to play a positive role for women scientists in the IT sector. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The go</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">vernment and the third-sector </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">need to work with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">them to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">address this jointly, through more scholarships and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> internships,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> better recognition of achievement of women in STEM sectors, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">dedicated professional networking opportunities, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and more family-friendly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">working policies </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to allow for a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">better </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">work-life balance.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">References</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">AAUW (2000) American Association of Un</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">iversity Women, Tech-savvy: Educating girls in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">new computer age 2000 [Online], Available at: www.aau</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">w.org/2000/techsavvy.html </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Barker, L and Weston, T (2003) ‘Institutional Effects and Participation of Women in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Computer Science’, Work in progress [Online], Available at: </span><span style="font-family:'Times N